  • Method Details

    • getData

      public void getData(Appointment passedApt, User user)
      Gets data passed from the AppointmentOverviewForm. When the scene changes from the main stage (AppointmentOverview) from am action event, this method gets all the data (objects) passed to it, so it can reference this data in the new scene. Used to grab the info from an existing appointment and display the existing data in the fields.
      Parameters:
      passedApt - Appointment that was selected on the appointment table when "Modify Appointment" was clicked
      user - Current logged in user to ensure logging of updates are handled correctly.

    • getData

      public void getData(User user)
      Getting Data from mainStage when "Add Appointment" is clicked. This is a overridden method to allow the reuse of the same appointment form whether "Modify Appointment" or "Add Appointment" is clicked. This method allows the passing of JUST the current user, since there is no appointment to pass when a new appointment is being made.
      Parameters:
      user - Current logged in user. To ensure accurate reporting on updates

    • startDate

      public void startDate(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
      Gets value of StartDate date picker field. Sets the value of datepicker field to a local variable @selectedStartDate to be used by other methods Then sets the endDate picker as enabled (validation), and pre-sets the date as the same day (but can be changed).
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - triggered when the date picker is clicked and a date is selected.

    • saveNewAppointment

      public void saveNewAppointment(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
      Appointment Form Handler When Saved Validates the form to ensure no empty text fields or comboBoxes. Also validates the appoitnment dates/times to reduce error. If validation passes, it determines is this is a modification or addition by checking the form label text value. Then submits the form data to the Appointment handler to be updated/added to the DB.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent -
